{"name":"Accurate Attack","type":"advantage","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"<p>COMBAT</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>When you make an accurate attack (see <strong>Maneuvers</strong>, page 249) you can take a penalty of up to &ndash;5 on the effect modifier of the attack and add the same number (up to +5) to your attack bonus.</p>","rank":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ivZkLTCCWgCEEUbG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"1NxUcJVF5NZTOKuh"}
{"name":"Skill Mastery (Acrobatics)","type":"advantage","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"<p>SKILL</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Choose a skill. You can make routine checks with that skill even when under pressure (see <strong>Routine Checks</strong> in <strong>The Basics</strong> chapter). This advantage does not allow you to make routine checks with skills that do not normally allow you to do so. You can take this advantage multiple times for different skills.</p>","rank":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ivZkLTCCWgCEEUbG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"5KBnoAruBt4Wq1tl"}
{"name":"Evasion","type":"advantage","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"<p>COMBAT, RANKED (2)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>You have a +2 circumstance bonus to Dodge resistance checks to avoid area effects (see the <strong>Area</strong> extra in the <strong>Powers</strong> chapter). If you have 2 ranks in this advantage, your circumstance bonus increases to +5.</p>","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ivZkLTCCWgCEEUbG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"9Ia2ZJ4DH3UuWPRz"}
{"name":"Defensive Roll","type":"advantage","img":"icons/svg/falling.svg","data":{"description":"<p>COMBAT, RANKED</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>You can avoid damage through agility and &ldquo;rolling&rdquo; with an attack. You receive a bonus to your Toughness equal to your advantage rank, but it is considered an active defense similar to Dodge and Parry (see <strong>Active Defenses</strong> in the <strong>Abilities</strong> chapter), so you lose this bonus whenever you are vulnerable or defenseless. Your total Toughness, including this advantage, is still limited by power level. This advantage is common for heroes who lack either superhuman speed or toughness, relying on their agility and training to avoid harm.</p>","rank":4},"effects":[{"_id":"ZXYVg8D8hL5AOMfW","changes":[{"key":"data.defences.tou.bonus","mode":2,"value":"4"}],"disabled":false,"duration":{"startTime":null},"icon":"icons/svg/falling.svg","label":"+4 Toughness","origin":"Item.3VNt4DUyFwHnzUny","transfer":true,"flags":{},"tint":null}],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ivZkLTCCWgCEEUbG":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.3VNt4DUyFwHnzUny"}},"_id":"Cm5EOEzDT68LnwZ9"}
{"name":"Precise Attack (Ranged Cover)","type":"advantage","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"<p>COMBAT, RANKED (4)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>When you make close or ranged attacks (choose one) you ignore attack check penalties for cover or concealment (choose one), although total cover still prevents you from making attacks. Each additional rank in this advantage lets you choose an additional option, so with Precise Attack 4, all your attacks (both close and ranged) ignore penalties for both cover and concealment.</p>","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ivZkLTCCWgCEEUbG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"N2iQAfGBxG9s8R6W"}
{"name":"Hide in Plain Sight","type":"advantage","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"<p>SKILL</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>You can hide (see <strong>Hiding</strong> under <strong>Stealth</strong> in the <strong>Skills</strong> chapter) without any need for a Deception or Intimidation check or any sort of diversion, and without penalty to your Stealth check. You&rsquo;re literally there one moment, and gone the next. You must still have some form of cover or concealment within range of your normal movement speed in order to hide.</p>","rank":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ivZkLTCCWgCEEUbG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"OXTNEjyVW9VMipQ4"}
{"name":"Improved Aim","type":"advantage","img":"icons/svg/target.svg","data":{"description":"<p>COMBAT</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>You have an even keener eye when it comes to ranged combat. When you take a standard action to aim, you gain double the normal circumstance bonus: +10 for a close attack or ranged attack adjacent to the target, +5 for a ranged attack at a greater distance. See <strong>Aim</strong>, page 246, for details.</p>","rank":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ivZkLTCCWgCEEUbG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"Qv8fnTVxB4vmVW5X"}
{"name":"Favored Enviroment (Urban)","type":"advantage","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"<p>COMBAT</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>You have an environment you&rsquo;re especially suited for fighting in. Examples include in the air, underwater, in space, in extreme heat or cold, in jungles or woodlands, and so forth. While you are in your favored environment, you gain a +2 circumstance bonus to attack checks or your active defenses. Choose at the start of the round whether the bonus applies to attack or defense. The choice remains until the start of your next round. This circumstance bonus is not affected by power level.</p>","rank":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ivZkLTCCWgCEEUbG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"UNYgVNlRxJ1Nthu8"}
{"name":"Move-by Action","type":"advantage","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"<p>COMBAT</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>When taking a standard action and a move action you can move both before and after your standard action, provided the total distance moved isn&rsquo;t greater than your normal movement speed.</p>","rank":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ivZkLTCCWgCEEUbG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"VajoK6wVaued1BEE"}
{"name":"Power Attack","type":"advantage","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"<p>COMBAT</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>When you make a power attack (see <strong>Maneuvers</strong>, page 250) you can take a penalty of up to &ndash;5 on your attack bonus and add the same number (up to +5) to the effect bonus of your attack.</p>","rank":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ivZkLTCCWgCEEUbG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"VyQtsKBcHiJAapjJ"}
{"name":"Equipment","type":"advantage","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"<p>GENERAL, RANKED</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>You have 5 points per rank in this advantage to spend on equipment. This includes vehicles and headquarters. See the <strong>Gadgets &amp; Gear</strong> chapter for details on equipment and its costs. Many heroes rely almost solely on Equipment in conjunction with their skills and other advantages</p>","rank":2},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ivZkLTCCWgCEEUbG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"kdpJk2SAVWN0ciDw"}
{"name":"Attractive","type":"advantage","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"<p>SKILL, RANKED (2)</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>You&rsquo;re particularly attractive, giving you a +2 circumstance bonus on Deception and Persuasion checks to deceive, seduce, or change the attitude of anyone who finds your looks appealing. With a second rank, you are Very Attractive, giving you a +5 circumstance bonus. This bonus does not count as part of your regular skill bonus in terms of the series power level, but also does not apply to people or situations which (in the GM&rsquo;s opinion) would not be influenced by your appearance. While superheroes tend to be a fairly good-looking lot, this advantage is generally reserved for characters with particularly impressive looks</p>","rank":1},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ivZkLTCCWgCEEUbG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"mp7hUMJuFw7jPWFC"}
{"name":"Uncanny Dodge","type":"advantage","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"<p>COMBAT</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>You are especially attuned to danger. You are not vulnerable when surprised or otherwise caught off-guard. You are still made vulnerable by effects that limit your mobility</p>","rank":null},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ivZkLTCCWgCEEUbG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"zCKnZVbY1jGcGAzm"}
{"name":"Improved Critical (Bow and Arrow)","type":"advantage","img":"icons/svg/item-bag.svg","data":{"description":"<p>COMBAT, RANKED</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Increase your critical threat range with a particular attack (chosen when you acquire this advantage) by 1, allowing you to score a critical hit on a natural 19 or 20. Only a natural 20 is an automatic hit, however, and an attack that misses is not a critical. Each additional rank applies to a different attack or increases your threat range with an existing attack by one more, to a maximum threat range of 16-20 with 4 ranks</p>","rank":4},"effects":[],"folder":null,"sort":0,"permission":{"default":0,"ivZkLTCCWgCEEUbG":3},"flags":{},"_id":"zZHdz0SHQmK2g4Km"}
